We hardly have any case to work on these days.

257
00:19:51,234 --> 00:19:51,942
Yeah.

258
00:19:52,125 --> 00:19:53,520
Let’s find some time and go on a trip together.

259
00:19:54,445 --> 00:19:57,954
Maybe it would help Tharn and Phaya...

260
00:19:58,137 --> 00:19:59,980
to get closer to each other when they are both naked.

261
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:06,502
Eat this! So that you can keep your mouth shut.

262
00:20:07,530 --> 00:20:09,771
Geez! What the fuck!

263
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:11,325
Damn you.

264
00:20:11,817 --> 00:20:12,788
Yai.

265
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,885
Has Tharn ever have a boyfriend or girlfriend before?

266
00:20:20,891 --> 00:20:22,925
Yes, but that person was dead.

267
00:20:23,954 --> 00:20:25,240
- Dead?   /   - Yes

268
00:20:27,337 --> 00:20:31,900
So, he’s afraid. He doesn’t want to get hurt like that again.

269
00:20:36,434 --> 00:20:38,994
What’s wrong with you, Miss Paranee?

270
00:20:38,990 --> 00:20:40,777
Why are you so interested in Dao?

271
00:20:41,131 --> 00:20:43,097
Don’t try to be a shipper.

272
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:44,251
I’m leaving.

273
00:20:44,251 --> 00:20:45,860
You’re changing the subject.

274
00:20:50,860 --> 00:20:57,820
The Sign
MingErTeamSub
Eng Trans @ThesignIDF

275
00:20:57,942 --> 00:21:04,922
The Sign

276
00:21:10,529 --> 00:21:12,541
These fruits are fresh from the market.

277
00:21:12,541 --> 00:21:14,369
My aunt asked me to send her best regards to you.

278
00:21:14,361 --> 00:21:15,215
Thank you.

279
00:21:15,923 --> 00:21:18,826
- That one is for Phaya.
- Thanks a lot.

280
00:21:19,192 --> 00:21:21,752
Phaya is injured from work again.

281
00:21:21,901 --> 00:21:24,335
So, my aunt told me to pay a visit as soon as I can.

282
00:21:24,655 --> 00:21:27,832
It seems like you had already known beforehand that he’d be injured.

283
00:21:28,312 --> 00:21:31,889
Well, that day when I went to see him at the unit,

284
00:21:32,015 --> 00:21:34,598
I remember he was also injured from work.

285
00:21:34,701 --> 00:21:40,815
I had a hunch that someone hot-tempered like him
would eventually get himself injured again.

286
00:21:41,112 --> 00:21:44,243
Well, I’m fine now.

287
00:21:45,295 --> 00:21:50,792
That’s why I didn’t tell you. I don’t want to bother you or anyone else.

288
00:21:51,466 --> 00:21:54,849
Whether it’s a big or small injury, our parents will always be worried about us.

289
00:21:58,929 --> 00:22:03,021
Grandma, I think we should ask him to quit being a cop.

290
00:22:03,051 --> 00:22:07,123
He has just started working and look how often he got injured.

291
00:22:08,506 --> 00:22:12,632
I’m afraid I won’t be able to stop him since it’s the job that he likes.

292
00:22:13,192 --> 00:22:16,266
I don’t like to force anyone to do something against his will.

293
00:22:16,381 --> 00:22:19,821
He’s free to do whatever he loves...

294
00:22:20,381 --> 00:22:24,666
as long as it’s not so dangerous that he has to risk his life for it.

295
00:22:26,472 --> 00:22:28,426
I totally agree with you.

296
00:22:28,941 --> 00:22:31,535
You can do any job you like.

297
00:22:31,878 --> 00:22:34,095
But you must also have a work-life balance.

298
00:22:34,186 --> 00:22:40,769
Don’t devote yourself to work so much that you forget
to care about those around you, or someone close to you.

299
00:22:40,826 --> 00:22:41,729
Do you agree?

300
00:22:43,226 --> 00:22:49,009
If you really love your job as a police officer,
maybe you should find someone to take care of you.

301
00:22:49,249 --> 00:22:52,381
So that he or she can look after you when you get injured again.

302
00:22:54,011 --> 00:22:57,489
Well, he has both Grandma and I to look after him.

303
00:22:57,672 --> 00:22:59,181
So, you don’t have to worry about that.

304
00:23:01,032 --> 00:23:03,969
Nee, listen to me.

305
00:23:04,563 --> 00:23:07,821
You also need to live your own life.

306
00:23:08,312 --> 00:23:10,861
You can’t spend your whole life looking after your big brother.

307
00:23:11,211 --> 00:23:14,506
Unless you don’t want to have anyone.

308
00:23:16,998 --> 00:23:18,918
Please excuse me for being rude.

309
00:23:19,009 --> 00:23:21,638
But I was wondering if you’re already taken?

310
00:23:24,735 --> 00:23:25,683
Well...

311
00:23:26,883 --> 00:23:28,323
Taken? A naughty girl like her?

312
00:23:28,929 --> 00:23:29,946
Obviously, not.

313
00:23:30,221 --> 00:23:31,981
Thank you so much for your concern about me though.

314
00:23:35,969 --> 00:23:38,883
All right then. Let’s start eating. We’ve been chatting for quite some time.

315
00:23:39,261 --> 00:23:40,049
Okay.

316
00:23:48,506 --> 00:23:49,821
Eat this too, Grandma.

317
00:23:57,009 --> 00:23:59,801
You should eat more so that you’d get better soon.

318
00:24:01,718 --> 00:24:02,552
Thank you.

319
00:24:09,283 --> 00:24:10,289
Thanks.

320
00:24:12,601 --> 00:24:14,003
You should eat more too.

321
00:24:14,415 --> 00:24:17,249
You probably didn’t get to eat Thai food that often when you were abroad.

322
00:24:17,241 --> 00:24:21,443
Oh, but I actually did. I worked part-time at a Thai restuarant.

323
00:24:28,821 --> 00:24:30,746
Grandma.

324
00:24:31,706 --> 00:24:36,575
My aunt told me that you will also attend the art exhibition. Is that right?

325
00:24:37,169 --> 00:24:41,866
Yes. Your aunt called and invited me by herself.

326
00:24:43,352 --> 00:24:46,106
Will Phaya be there too?

327
00:24:46,101 --> 00:24:48,781
My aunt said you’ll also take him with you.

328
00:24:48,975 --> 00:24:50,095
Ah, that’s right.

329
00:24:53,866 --> 00:24:57,523
Can you please come with me? My friends really want to see you.

330
00:24:57,851 --> 00:25:01,123
You hardly go anywhere with me these days.

331
00:25:01,226 --> 00:25:02,826
All you do is work.

332
00:25:03,638 --> 00:25:05,226
Well...I...

333
00:25:09,981 --> 00:25:13,078
Of course, Grandma. I’ll go with you.

334
00:25:17,683 --> 00:25:21,169
I’m also free.

335
00:25:22,929 --> 00:25:24,049
Can I go too?

336
00:25:25,363 --> 00:25:26,186
Of course.

337
00:25:51,261 --> 00:25:53,443
Can’t he just at least send me a sticker?

338
00:26:15,123 --> 00:26:16,209
(Door scratching)

339
00:26:17,661 --> 00:26:19,306
(Door scratching)

340
00:26:30,175 --> 00:26:31,432
Nee?

341
00:26:36,391 --> 00:26:37,078
What’s the matter?

342
00:26:38,666 --> 00:26:43,306
I bring you some fruits that Dao gave us.

343
00:26:44,689 --> 00:26:47,809
Hmm, are you really my sister?

344
00:26:48,883 --> 00:26:50,312
Why are you so kind today?

345
00:26:51,215 --> 00:26:54,723
This is all you’d get to eat. The rest is mine.

346
00:26:55,721 --> 00:26:58,335
Thanks a lot. Put it over there. I’ll eat them soon.

347
00:27:13,443 --> 00:27:17,592
Aren’t you done? Go back to your room then.

348
00:27:19,672 --> 00:27:20,632
I’m not in a hurry.

349
00:27:20,963 --> 00:27:24,163
Your room looks so comfy today.

350
00:27:33,238 --> 00:27:34,083
What?

351
00:27:34,266 --> 00:27:35,158
Eat this first.

352
00:27:41,489 --> 00:27:42,163
Eat it.

353
00:27:44,191 --> 00:27:44,986
What is it?

354
00:27:44,981 --> 00:27:46,191
I’ll get to the point then.

355
00:27:46,209 --> 00:27:46,975
Okay.

356
00:27:48,643 --> 00:27:52,323
How close were you and Dao when you two were studying abroad?

357
00:27:58,161 --> 00:28:03,089
Grandma asked me to take care of her because she’s the favourite niece of her best friend. That’s all.

358
00:28:04,929 --> 00:28:07,398
Have you and Dao ever been together?

359
00:28:08,643 --> 00:28:11,683
You are quite a player. So, I think it’s possible.

360
00:28:11,706 --> 00:28:14,175
- Geez, you monkey.   /    - Ouch.

361
00:28:14,723 --> 00:28:15,672
That’s enough.

362
00:28:16,883 --> 00:28:19,466
Just answer my question so that I can be at ease.

363
00:28:20,735 --> 00:28:23,558
No, Dao and I are like brother and sister.

364
00:28:26,026 --> 00:28:28,301
Okay, I feel better now.

365
00:28:31,592 --> 00:28:35,763
What’s wrong with you, Miss Paranee?

366
00:28:36,563 --> 00:28:38,358
Why are you so interested in Dao?

367
00:28:39,992 --> 00:28:46,381
Well, she is beautiful and seems to know you well.

368
00:28:46,712 --> 00:28:49,398
Our Grandma seems to like her a lot too.

369
00:28:49,958 --> 00:28:53,592
So, I just want to know more about her.

370
00:28:53,946 --> 00:28:55,386
That’s all.

371
00:28:57,009 --> 00:29:00,232
She and you would probably make a perfect couple though.

372
00:29:01,295 --> 00:29:02,963
I mean, consdisering all other factors.

373
00:29:03,981 --> 00:29:07,078
She’s actually too good for someone like you.

374
00:29:09,581 --> 00:29:12,449
But good enough for you, right?

375
00:29:13,135 --> 00:29:14,061
What?

376
00:29:20,266 --> 00:29:21,295
What?

377
00:29:22,049 --> 00:29:23,946
Don’t try to be a shipper.

378
00:29:24,431 --> 00:29:25,078
I’m leaving.

379
00:29:25,071 --> 00:29:26,861
You’re changing the subject.

380
00:29:26,861 --> 00:29:30,038
Namami. Where’s Namami?

381
00:29:30,358 --> 00:29:32,163
Where’d he go?

382
00:29:39,569 --> 00:29:40,781
Who’s this girl?

383
00:29:44,438 --> 00:29:46,998
And this guy too.

384
00:29:47,701 --> 00:29:51,546
Hmm, that girl is the one I often dream of.

385
00:29:51,901 --> 00:29:53,901
That guy is my colleague.

386
00:29:54,838 --> 00:30:01,672
Ahh, is he the one you were rushing out to see this evening?

387
00:30:02,849 --> 00:30:04,141
Yeah.

388
00:30:04,712 --> 00:30:08,952
I just feel that these two have something in common.

389
00:30:09,683 --> 00:30:14,483
Huh? But this girl is just someone from your dream.

390
00:30:16,426 --> 00:30:17,661
That’s right.

391
00:30:18,849 --> 00:30:25,558
Hang on. Are you saying that you’re worried about your colleague whose name is Tharn?

392
00:30:25,866 --> 00:30:28,552
So much that you try to relate him with a girl you often see in your dream?

393
00:30:29,443 --> 00:30:32,792
Is this the answer you’ve always been looking for?

394
00:30:33,341 --> 00:30:36,163
To find out who or what it is that you saw when you were drowning.

395
00:30:39,958 --> 00:30:41,226
Nee.

396
00:30:42,483 --> 00:30:47,158
Is your friend, Wi, still teaching at the Faculty of Archaeology?

397
00:30:48,861 --> 00:30:52,952
The one you used to say she was cute?

398
00:30:53,718 --> 00:30:54,403
Yeah.

399
00:30:55,306 --> 00:31:02,415
When we last talked, she said she would quit to open an art gallery.

400
00:31:03,146 --> 00:31:04,141
Why?

401
00:31:22,511 --> 00:31:24,146
Are you sure?

402
00:31:25,221 --> 00:31:29,851
Yes, I am. My gallery has never bought or displayed this kind of art.

403
00:31:31,181 --> 00:31:33,741
But I was told that it was sold here.

404
00:31:37,946 --> 00:31:42,769
I’d still insist that my gallery has never bought that kind of art.

405
00:31:43,706 --> 00:31:47,261
You can search the gallery if you want to.

406
00:31:48,632 --> 00:31:50,312
You’re not lying to me, aren’t you?

407
00:31:55,043 --> 00:31:56,681
No, I’m not lying.

408
00:32:20,615 --> 00:32:21,631
Hey.

409
00:32:22,992 --> 00:32:24,161
Phaya.

410
00:32:26,541 --> 00:32:27,375
Wi.

411
00:32:33,375 --> 00:32:35,112
How are you doing?

412
00:32:35,283 --> 00:32:36,323
I’m good.

413
00:32:36,826 --> 00:32:38,321
Long time no see.

414
00:32:38,586 --> 00:32:40,495
It’s been over a year, I think.

415
00:32:40,746 --> 00:32:44,529
I’m sorry for a sudden visit. I also come empty-handed.

416
00:32:47,603 --> 00:32:52,129
By the way, that man looks very suspicious.

417
00:32:53,146 --> 00:32:54,941
He’s looking for his artwork.

418
00:32:55,203 --> 00:32:57,832
He said his girlfriend sold it to my gallery.

419
00:32:58,358 --> 00:33:00,289
But I’ve never bought any artwork from his girlfriend.

420
00:33:01,272 --> 00:33:04,266
This happens a lot in the art industry.

421
00:33:04,792 --> 00:33:06,792
Stealing someone else’s works and sell them.

422
00:33:06,801 --> 00:33:11,649
Some are rare antiques which the owners have no idea how valuable they are.

423
00:33:11,672 --> 00:33:14,301
Those with a keen eye would buy them and resell at a much higher price.

424
00:33:14,575 --> 00:33:17,501
When the owners of the work found out, they often came out to claim their rights of ownership.

425
00:33:18,026 --> 00:33:21,089
But some of them are forged. They are fake ones.

426
00:33:21,409 --> 00:33:25,123
You can hardly tell them apart from the original works though.

427
00:33:26,883 --> 00:33:30,415
It sounds quite complicated but I got it somehow.

428
00:33:31,123 --> 00:33:33,683
There’s always a story hidden behind each artwork.

429
00:33:34,083 --> 00:33:39,238
Each has its own unique value, method, and expertise...

430
00:33:39,912 --> 00:33:42,986
depending on the artist who has created that piece of work.

431
00:33:42,998 --> 00:33:44,826
Those are what make the artwork valuable.

432
00:33:45,169 --> 00:33:51,695
Is this why you decided to quit teaching at the university and open an art gallery instead?

433
00:33:52,541 --> 00:33:54,163
Not really.

434
00:33:55,729 --> 00:34:00,072
Why do you come to see me? Is there anything I can help?

435
00:34:15,581 --> 00:34:18,255
If it were told by someone else, I wouldn’t have believed a word.

436
00:34:19,146 --> 00:34:22,186
That all your dreams seem to be connected.

437
00:34:23,523 --> 00:34:27,055
Do you have any idea now that you have seen my sketches?

438
00:34:29,843 --> 00:34:37,089
Archaeology is the study of human past through landscapes, architectures, and other material remain...

439
00:34:37,523 --> 00:34:39,866
with traces of culture in the past.

440
00:34:40,918 --> 00:34:43,249
These are, however, what you saw in your dreams.

441
00:34:44,243 --> 00:34:46,483
I can’t believe they can be connected into a story like this.

442
00:34:47,151 --> 00:34:53,941
But what about the legend about Naga or the fireballs
which you can see on every 15th night of the 11th waxing moon?

443
00:34:54,575 --> 00:34:57,832
There are records and traces found that it actually happened, aren’t there?

444
00:34:58,221 --> 00:35:03,603
But those are proves for a living creature which is not human being.

445
00:35:03,621 --> 00:35:05,672
It’s just a legend told among the locals.

446
00:35:05,798 --> 00:35:12,495
Even for the Garuda. There’s hardly any record on this half-human and half-bird creature.

447
00:35:12,838 --> 00:35:16,609
Most are just stories found in the religious mythology…

448
00:35:16,701 --> 00:35:20,255
which cannot be proofed whether it’s true or not.

449
00:35:20,971 --> 00:35:23,352
So, I’m afraid I can’t help you much with this.

450
00:35:23,501 --> 00:35:25,821
I only say it from my point of view.

451
00:35:26,129 --> 00:35:27,855
It might actually exist.

452
00:35:28,301 --> 00:35:32,666
Like energy forces, souls, or miracles.

453
00:35:32,781 --> 00:35:36,449
They are things that science can’t proof.

454
00:35:36,601 --> 00:35:39,203
But there are stories told about them.

455
00:35:39,351 --> 00:35:43,238
Someone had witnessed those things and record what they saw.

456
00:35:45,203 --> 00:35:49,146
Can you tell me where to find more information about it?

457
00:35:54,221 --> 00:36:01,821
There’s a corner in my gallery where I keep all the records on ancient history.

458
00:36:01,961 --> 00:36:03,958
You can try looking in that room.

459
00:36:04,071 --> 00:36:08,552
You might find something useful there.

460
00:36:53,101 --> 00:37:02,941
(Mysterious Sound)

461
00:37:07,021 --> 00:37:08,146
(The sound of bookshelves shaking)

462
00:37:44,632 --> 00:37:46,312
Come with me.

463
00:37:46,311 --> 00:37:47,489
Let me go.

464
00:37:48,666 --> 00:37:50,232
What’s wrong with you?

465
00:37:53,215 --> 00:37:54,481
Let’s go.

466
00:37:54,481 --> 00:38:01,441
The Sign
