560
00:45:44,506 --> 00:45:51,486
The Sign

561
00:45:58,585 --> 00:46:01,196
This is the floor plan of the art exhibition at the BACC.

562
00:46:01,219 --> 00:46:04,282
It’s for the mission that I’ve informed you earlier.

563
00:46:05,065 --> 00:46:08,195
I need a volunteer for this mission.

564
00:46:08,195 --> 00:46:11,745
Our job is to protect the important people who would attend the event.

565
00:46:12,007 --> 00:46:13,687
This is a special mission.

566
00:46:13,893 --> 00:46:16,990
It’s not an order from the authority.

567
00:46:16,985 --> 00:46:18,876
That’s why I’m looking for a volunteer.

568
00:46:20,235 --> 00:46:21,927
Raise your hand if you want to volunteer.

569
00:46:29,125 --> 00:46:30,350
Are you listening?

570
00:46:32,365 --> 00:46:34,762
I asked if you were listening.

571
00:46:38,453 --> 00:46:40,705
He asked if you were listening to what he just said.

572
00:46:41,785 --> 00:46:44,773
I didn’t. But I was reading your lips.

573
00:46:44,875 --> 00:46:48,922
You want some volunteers to work on a special mission which is not an order from the authority.

574
00:46:49,075 --> 00:46:53,150
Their job is to protect the important people at the exhibition.

575
00:46:53,459 --> 00:46:57,767
Those who want to volunteer please raise their hands.

576
00:46:58,355 --> 00:47:00,270
(Clapping)
Wow!

577
00:47:00,419 --> 00:47:01,745
You’re like a bugging device.

578
00:47:03,893 --> 00:47:06,590
Then I’ll assume everyone already understood what the mission is.

579
00:47:07,310 --> 00:47:09,150
Give me the name list once it’s done.

580
00:47:16,625 --> 00:47:18,259
I want to do it.

581
00:47:18,739 --> 00:47:23,573
I don’t think it’d be just a simple bodyguard job.

582
00:47:24,727 --> 00:47:26,099
I agree.

583
00:47:26,727 --> 00:47:28,293
It’s very strange.

584
00:47:28,533 --> 00:47:31,596
Our unit has never taken any job like this before.

585
00:47:32,065 --> 00:47:33,276
I’m sure there must be something behind this.

586
00:47:34,899 --> 00:47:40,065
We are not allowed to reveal our identity as an IDF officer too.

587
00:47:41,539 --> 00:47:43,493
It’s going to be so interesting.

588
00:47:46,247 --> 00:47:47,687
You get to dress up nicely.

589
00:47:48,693 --> 00:47:50,407
And work at a nice building.

590
00:47:52,335 --> 00:47:54,865
After work, I will keep the suit on and take Sand to dinner at...

591
00:47:54,865 --> 00:47:55,733
the food stall in the gas station.

592
00:47:55,725 --> 00:47:57,733
Yeah. And order a spicy minced pork salad with lots of blood.

593
00:47:57,725 --> 00:48:00,670
Geez, you eat it yourself then. You got me carried away.

594
00:48:00,685 --> 00:48:02,727
You seem to be in a lovey dovey mode.

595
00:48:02,725 --> 00:48:03,962
Obviously.

596
00:48:04,405 --> 00:48:06,042
- Are you in then?
- Of course.

597
00:48:07,265 --> 00:48:09,025
- Singh, are you in?
- Yeah.

598
00:48:11,253 --> 00:48:15,642
- If my babe is going then I’ll go too.
- (Sigh)

599
00:48:18,705 --> 00:48:21,505
Are you going, Mayris?

600
00:48:23,215 --> 00:48:28,699
No, Inspector probably wants me to find out more information on the Lieutenant Tam’s case.

601
00:48:29,687 --> 00:48:30,556
Okay.

602
00:48:31,630 --> 00:48:32,876
Lieut Tam’s case?

603
00:48:34,316 --> 00:48:36,487
I thought the authority has ordered to have this case closed.

604
00:48:39,939 --> 00:48:41,927
They have.

605
00:48:41,950 --> 00:48:45,322
But the Inspector wants us keep investigating.

606
00:48:45,335 --> 00:48:51,756
Because Lieut Tam’s body might lead us to the major drug trafficking network backed up by politicians.

607
00:48:52,085 --> 00:48:54,922
Lieut Tam died in the line of duty.

608
00:48:56,485 --> 00:48:57,173
Huh?

609
00:48:57,585 --> 00:48:59,459
You guys didn’t know about this?

610
00:49:00,899 --> 00:49:04,339
Ahh, you came later.

611
00:49:05,333 --> 00:49:08,773
Apart from being a coach at our unit,

612
00:49:09,219 --> 00:49:12,053
Lieut Tam also had another important job in our IDF unit.

613
00:49:12,533 --> 00:49:15,379
He was one of the best spies we’ve ever had.

614
00:49:15,375 --> 00:49:18,293
And he was also the Inspector’s right-hand man.

615
00:49:18,285 --> 00:49:22,430
His mission was to track down the international drug trafficking network...

616
00:49:23,075 --> 00:49:27,162
of which Minister Montree is believed to be the man behind it.

617
00:49:29,665 --> 00:49:32,350
Songyod is also one of his minions.

618
00:49:32,705 --> 00:49:35,790
He’s actually the Minister’s hand and foot.

619
00:49:36,522 --> 00:49:39,116
Then why can’t we just go question Songyod and force him to tell us...

620
00:49:39,893 --> 00:49:43,459
information that could help destroy Minister Montree’s network?

621
00:49:44,442 --> 00:49:46,750
Our IDF unit’s main job is to investigate.

622
00:49:46,910 --> 00:49:48,430
The execution of judgement…

623
00:49:48,425 --> 00:49:52,099
or determination of punishment is the authority’s job.

624
00:49:52,122 --> 00:49:55,870
- Which we cannot...
- We cannot cross the line, right?

625
00:49:56,922 --> 00:50:00,065
Just like many cases in the past that were treated unfairly.

626
00:50:01,859 --> 00:50:05,276
Yeah, including your the case about your parents too.

627
00:50:09,653 --> 00:50:11,813
It’s a way to force us to go forward…

628
00:50:12,265 --> 00:50:15,127
but with a rope around our neck.

629
00:50:15,276 --> 00:50:17,710
They only allow us to walk in the direction that they are approved of.

630
00:50:18,430 --> 00:50:19,813
Fake freedom, you mean?

631
00:50:20,933 --> 00:50:23,470
Well then, I won’t be joining you guys this time.

632
00:50:23,465 --> 00:50:26,373
I have a more important job to do.

633
00:50:33,767 --> 00:50:34,670
(Sigh)

634
00:50:36,430 --> 00:50:37,516
I’m in.

635
00:50:38,945 --> 00:50:40,487
Then go and ask Phaya too.

636
00:50:41,070 --> 00:50:42,933
I think he probably wants to join us too.

637
00:50:43,310 --> 00:50:45,333
You go and ask him yourself.

638
00:50:47,802 --> 00:50:49,722
Yai.

639
00:50:52,065 --> 00:50:53,699
When did they quarrel?

640
00:50:53,695 --> 00:50:55,070
Was it at his condo?

641
00:50:55,973 --> 00:50:57,139
Do you really want to know?

642
00:50:57,425 --> 00:50:59,475
It’s my job to know about other people’s businesses.

643
00:50:59,475 --> 00:51:01,790
Then you go and ask him. I don’t want to mention it.

644
00:51:02,293 --> 00:51:06,785
Geez! You two are the same.

645
00:51:07,687 --> 00:51:08,910
I’ll ask baby then.

646
00:51:09,135 --> 00:51:10,487
Baby, Tharn and…

647
00:51:10,485 --> 00:51:14,225
Stop. You’re bothering me. Go away.

648
00:51:19,585 --> 00:51:21,459
- That’s a lot.
- Yeah.

649
00:51:28,819 --> 00:51:32,099
Inspector never disappoints us. His special mission is so cool.

650
00:51:32,487 --> 00:51:34,015
I don’t want to hold a gun tonight.

651
00:51:34,015 --> 00:51:36,122
I’d rather hold her instead. Oops!

652
00:51:36,259 --> 00:51:40,007
If you don’t want to spend a night in a coffin, you’d better quit playing around.

653
00:51:40,876 --> 00:51:42,019
- Baby.
- Good luck.

654
00:51:44,933 --> 00:51:46,579
- I’ll go check on the other side.
- Okay.

655
00:51:47,779 --> 00:51:51,836
If you are mad at him, you should clear it up with him when he comes to work tomorrow.

656
00:51:52,053 --> 00:51:53,390
I don’t have anything to say to him.

657
00:51:53,459 --> 00:51:56,682
Nothing to say? But your face already said it all.

658
00:51:56,933 --> 00:51:59,219
He did that because he was worried about you.

659
00:51:59,459 --> 00:52:01,539
Hey, Yai. Tharn.

660
00:52:02,099 --> 00:52:03,219
You guys are here too?

661
00:52:04,705 --> 00:52:07,885
Phaya? What on earth are you doing here?

662
00:52:08,190 --> 00:52:09,436
I’m a guest.

663
00:52:09,767 --> 00:52:12,922
This is my grandmother and my little sister.

664
00:52:13,607 --> 00:52:15,299
- Hello.    /   - Hello.

665
00:52:16,205 --> 00:52:20,225
Inspector has asked our team to help taking care of the security at the event.

666
00:52:23,139 --> 00:52:25,845
Excuse me? Are you Tharn?

667
00:52:27,105 --> 00:52:29,882
It’s been a long time since we last met. Do you still remember me?

668
00:52:29,895 --> 00:52:31,242
Of course, I do.

669
00:52:31,255 --> 00:52:37,047
Phaya only told me that he met a friend who saved his life when he was a kid.

670
00:52:37,065 --> 00:52:41,470
I didn’t know that you also work at the same unit. The world is round indeed.

671
00:52:42,155 --> 00:52:44,785
Well, it might not be because the world is round...

672
00:52:44,922 --> 00:52:48,876
but rather a destiny that brought these two together.

673
00:52:49,299 --> 00:52:50,522
Ouch.

674
00:52:51,135 --> 00:52:53,505
- Um...   /   - Ouch.

675
00:52:55,325 --> 00:52:59,459
I can remember your face but not your name.

676
00:52:59,465 --> 00:53:02,179
- This is Yai, Grandma.
- You’re...

677
00:53:02,185 --> 00:53:05,605
- Yes.
- Another kid at the temple who also saved me that day.

678
00:53:05,805 --> 00:53:11,676
Oh, I see. Now that all of you live in Bangkok, we should see each other more often.

679
00:53:11,865 --> 00:53:15,139
Please come to my place for a meal whenever you’re free.

680
00:53:15,276 --> 00:53:19,985
I’d like to treat you both to a meal as a thank you for saving my grandson.

681
00:53:20,682 --> 00:53:21,985
Thank you very much, Grandma.

682
00:53:22,579 --> 00:53:24,979
I’m afraid we have to get back to work now.

683
00:53:25,162 --> 00:53:27,516
Go on, dear.

684
00:53:27,642 --> 00:53:29,070
- Goodbye.   /   - Goodbye.

685
00:53:29,065 --> 00:53:29,962
See you.

686
00:53:32,605 --> 00:53:37,093
- Grandma, please wait here for a second. I’ll be right back.
- Okay.

687
00:53:44,065 --> 00:53:45,059
Tharn.

688
00:53:47,733 --> 00:53:48,762
Can we talk?

689
00:53:51,225 --> 00:53:52,670
You guys talk then.

690
00:53:53,493 --> 00:53:54,819
You can do it!

691
00:53:56,979 --> 00:53:57,916
What is it?

692
00:53:59,882 --> 00:54:02,042
Well, about that night...

693
00:54:03,722 --> 00:54:05,425
I’m sorry.

694
00:54:06,979 --> 00:54:10,030
The one you should apologise to is him not me.

695
00:54:10,453 --> 00:54:11,859
But the one I care about is you.

696
00:54:11,855 --> 00:54:13,470
Why do you have to mention him?

697
00:54:13,653 --> 00:54:14,835
Phaya.

698
00:54:17,287 --> 00:54:18,887
When did you arrive?

699
00:54:19,459 --> 00:54:21,379
My aunt is looking for you.

700
00:54:21,539 --> 00:54:23,242
Where are Grandma and Nee?

701
00:54:24,099 --> 00:54:27,013
Is this your colleague?

702
00:54:27,493 --> 00:54:29,413
- Hello.   /   - Hello.

703
00:54:31,195 --> 00:54:32,510
- I’ll go then.    /   - Hey.

704
00:54:34,053 --> 00:54:34,750
Tharn!

705
00:54:35,215 --> 00:54:38,465
Grandma and Nee are over there.

706
00:54:38,465 --> 00:54:39,825
Please excuse me. I’ll go talk to my colleague first.

707
00:54:45,402 --> 00:54:46,305
Tharn.

708
00:54:48,213 --> 00:54:51,047
Doc? You’re here too?

709
00:54:52,076 --> 00:54:53,219
I got invited.

710
00:54:54,275 --> 00:54:58,750
It’s an exhibition displaying artworks which reflect on the human’s state of mind.

711
00:54:59,105 --> 00:55:03,215
- Let’s go inside then.
- Okay.

712
00:55:14,350 --> 00:55:15,996
Whom is Phaya talking to?

713
00:55:17,516 --> 00:55:20,053
Is that the girl who came to see him at the unit?

714
00:55:26,385 --> 00:55:27,573
Doctor Chalothorn.

715
00:55:28,979 --> 00:55:29,356
Yes?

716
00:55:29,355 --> 00:55:31,447
Someone wants to see you over there.

717
00:55:32,293 --> 00:55:33,127
Okay.

718
00:55:34,636 --> 00:55:37,607
I’m leaving then. I’ll call you after the event.

719
00:55:38,579 --> 00:55:39,425
Okay.

720
00:55:40,339 --> 00:55:41,105
This way, please.

721
00:55:47,745 --> 00:55:49,287
Probably just a friend.

722
00:55:50,499 --> 00:55:52,202
He’s still single, isn’t he?

723
00:55:54,636 --> 00:55:56,762
It has nothing to do with me anyway.

724
00:55:58,956 --> 00:56:02,750
Hmm, are you sure?

725
00:56:03,036 --> 00:56:04,693
Look at your face first.

726
00:56:04,830 --> 00:56:08,099
Your face and eyes just say it all.

727
00:56:08,453 --> 00:56:09,745
Tell me honestly,

728
00:56:10,419 --> 00:56:12,602
why would you resist your own feelings?

729
00:56:13,082 --> 00:56:14,305
Love is love.

730
00:56:15,685 --> 00:56:20,865
I want to see you happy again, Tharn.

731
00:56:21,219 --> 00:56:25,025
I want to see you smile like you used to.

732
00:56:26,019 --> 00:56:30,693
If you’re afraid that loving him would put him in danger,

733
00:56:31,093 --> 00:56:34,015
I’ll also help you protect him.

734
00:56:37,676 --> 00:56:38,922
No need.

735
00:56:41,025 --> 00:56:44,693
I’ll do it because I want to see my brother happy.

736
00:56:45,653 --> 00:56:46,750
Got it?

737
00:57:10,925 --> 00:57:14,510
Don’t forget to remind the others to keep an eye on the artworks too.

738
00:57:14,505 --> 00:57:15,779
(Something drops)

739
00:57:16,362 --> 00:57:17,310
I’m sorry.

740
00:57:24,750 --> 00:57:25,847
It's OK.

741
00:57:51,390 --> 00:57:54,339
What a pleasure to meet you again, Inspector.

742
00:57:54,745 --> 00:57:56,247
Hello, Mr. Montree.

743
00:57:56,865 --> 00:58:00,105
Have we met before? You look so familiar.

744
00:58:00,105 --> 00:58:02,967
Let me remind you again that your job today...

745
00:58:02,985 --> 00:58:06,853
is to protect the safety of important guests who attend the event.

746
00:58:09,985 --> 00:58:11,465
Arghhhh!!!

747
00:58:12,005 --> 00:58:15,779
Love doesn’t exist. They are all lies.

748
00:58:16,105 --> 00:58:20,739
You must pay for what you did.

749
00:58:35,555 --> 00:58:43,230
🎵I will always cherish this love in my heart.🎵

750
00:58:43,225 --> 00:58:50,670
🎵No matter for how long, I’ll always want to see you.🎵

751
00:58:50,665 --> 00:58:59,059
🎵I want you to know that you are the one that I want.🎵

752
00:58:59,059 --> 00:59:09,205
🎵I’m going to love you and only you.🎵

753
00:59:09,505 --> 00:59:16,922
🎵No matter for how lond, it will never change.🎵

754
00:59:16,915 --> 00:59:21,379
🎵Whether in my sleep or while I’m awake.🎵

755
00:59:21,605 --> 00:59:24,522
🎵I’ll never forget you.🎵

756
00:59:24,515 --> 00:59:31,973
🎵No matter for how long, I’ll always love you.🎵

757
00:59:31,973 --> 00:59:36,205
🎵Love you with all my heart.🎵

758
00:59:36,205 --> 00:59:44,125
🎵No one can take your place because my heart belongs to you.🎵

759
00:59:44,125 --> 00:59:47,085
